                                             ...... First of all Cyber Security and Ethical Hacking, Its all about Interest and Passion ......

Educational Foundation:

        High School,
        Bachelor’s Degree: Consider degrees in Computer Science, Information Technology, or Cybersecurity.
        (I suggest do certifications in final year of your college) Certifications: Get certified with recognized credentials such as CompTIA Security+, Certified Ethical Hacker (CEH), Offensive Security Certified Professional (OSCP), etc.

    Learn the Basics of Networking and Security:

        Understand networking like protocols (TCP/IP, HTTP, FTP, etc.),Switches, Routers, Servers, etc......... 
        Study operating systems like (Windows, Linux, macOS).
        Learn about firewalls, intrusion detection/prevention systems, and encryption techniques learn about Crypotography.

    Develop Programming Skills:

        Learn languages such as Python, C, C++, JavaScript, and Bash scripting.(For Automation and write your own sripting)
        Understand SQL for database manipulation and vulnerability testing.

    Gain Practical Experience:

        Set up a home lab to practice hacking skills legally.
        Participate in Capture The Flag (CTF) competitions.(Over the wire)
        Contribute to open-source security projects.
        Intern with cybersecurity firms or IT departments.

    Stay Updated:

        Follow cybersecurity blogs, forums, and news sources.
        Join professional networks like ISACA, (ISC)², and local cybersecurity meetups.

    Build a Portfolio:

        Document your projects and experiences.(Project may based on Cyber Security like Key logger, Network analyzer,  Password cracker  etc.......)
        Maintain a blog or GitHub repository showcasing your work.

    Legal and Ethical Knowledge:

                              (Have a HACKER mindset but used in an ethical way)

        Understand the laws and regulations related to cybersecurity and ethical hacking.
        Always practice ethical hacking within legal boundaries.

Career Opportunities in Ethical Hacking

    Penetration Tester: Simulate cyberattacks to find vulnerabilities in systems.
    Security Consultant: Advise organizations on how to protect their systems.
    Security Analyst: Monitor and protect an organization’s digital infrastructure.
    Incident Responder: Address and mitigate security breaches when they occur.
    Forensic Analyst: Investigate and analyze cybercrimes.

Key Resources

    Youtube channels:
                                                  
